Oh, the rice isn't done.

00:29:38.543 --> 00:29:39.811
Narrator:
Fast on the heels

00:29:39.811 --> 00:29:41.212
of their child's birth,

00:29:41.212 --> 00:29:44.082
parents confront
another stressful obstacle...

00:29:44.082 --> 00:29:45.884
Alright, Naham, we're coming!

00:29:45.884 --> 00:29:47.318
Narrator:
...the lack of quality,

00:29:47.318 --> 00:29:49.254
affordable childcare.

00:29:49.254 --> 00:29:50.421
Man:
We were first looking

00:29:50.421 --> 00:29:53.258
at daycare when
Yaminette was pregnant.

00:29:53.258 --> 00:29:54.225
For over a year...

00:29:55.794 --> 00:29:58.062
Narrator:
Of forty-five nations,

00:29:58.062 --> 00:30:02.634
the United States ranks 31st
in availability of childcare,

00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:05.103
16th in affordability,

00:30:05.103 --> 00:30:08.239
and most alarmingly for
our children's development,

00:30:08.239 --> 00:30:11.232
22nd in quality.

00:30:11.576 --> 00:30:12.577
I love you, brother!

00:30:12.577 --> 00:30:13.645
Narrator:
Yaminette and David

00:30:13.645 --> 00:30:16.247
are just starting life
as a family,

00:30:16.247 --> 00:30:18.516
raising their son Naham
and daughter Nikha.

00:30:18.516 --> 00:30:20.685
Naham:
...trying to find it...

00:30:20.685 --> 00:30:21.986
Yaminette:
Tomorrow's a hectic day.

00:30:21.986 --> 00:30:22.954
I have a training.

00:30:22.954 --> 00:30:25.657
I have to be there at 9 o'clock.

00:30:25.657 --> 00:30:26.925
Narrator:
Yaminette works full-time

00:30:26.925 --> 00:30:28.293
and more...

00:30:28.293 --> 00:30:30.595
Yaminette:
I bring work home with me.

00:30:30.595 --> 00:30:34.332
It's just what I do so that
I don't feel as overwhelmed.

00:30:34.332 --> 00:30:35.466
You need a fruit, Naham.

00:30:35.466 --> 00:30:36.534
Raspberries?

00:30:36.534 --> 00:30:38.469
Narrator:
David is on a fast track

00:30:38.469 --> 00:30:40.138
to finishing his education.

00:30:40.138 --> 00:30:41.806
Yaminette:
I'm the breadwinner.

00:30:41.806 --> 00:30:43.208
I'm the sugar mama.

00:30:43.208 --> 00:30:44.809
Hi, honey!

00:30:44.809 --> 00:30:47.545
Are you ready to try
something new?

00:30:47.545 --> 00:30:49.013
David:
The clock is ticking.

00:30:49.013 --> 00:30:51.482
The clock's ticking because
your bank account's running low,

00:30:51.482 --> 00:30:53.351
the clock's ticking because
you gotta build your career,

00:30:53.351 --> 00:30:55.720
but also,
once you have kids,

00:30:55.720 --> 00:30:57.655
you really want to invest
in those early years,

00:30:57.655 --> 00:30:59.988
you don't want to treat
that time cheaply.

00:31:00.692 --> 00:31:02.026
Narrator:
Most parents don't want

00:31:02.026 --> 00:31:03.695
to think of their
baby's well-being

00:31:03.695 --> 00:31:07.065
in terms of dollars,
but how can they not?

00:31:07.065 --> 00:31:10.902
Nationwide, center-based
childcare generally averages

00:31:10.902 --> 00:31:14.463
more than $10,000
a year per child.

00:31:15.506 --> 00:31:17.141
Yaminette:
With Naham, our first,

00:31:17.141 --> 00:31:21.079
we've consistently paid more
for childcare than for rent.

00:31:21.079 --> 00:31:22.180
Oh, yeah.

00:31:22.180 --> 00:31:23.348
Yaminette:
With Nikha,

00:31:23.348 --> 00:31:27.151
my name's on the waiting
list at two places.

00:31:27.151 --> 00:31:30.088
For Ellis, we were told
we're around number 40.

00:31:30.088 --> 00:31:34.389
I'm really, really holding out
for Ellis.

00:31:36.327 --> 00:31:37.829
Narrator:
Ellis is Ellis Memorial

00:31:37.829 --> 00:31:39.597
Child Development Center -

00:31:39.597 --> 00:31:42.367
one of Boston's best
and most affordable.

00:31:42.367 --> 00:31:45.203
Where's Henry?

00:31:45.203 --> 00:31:46.337
There's Henry!

00:31:46.337 --> 00:31:49.398
Narrator:
Demand for a spot here is high.

00:31:50.708 --> 00:31:52.043
Woman:
This is our wait list

00:31:52.043 --> 00:31:56.247
and this is the waitlist
just for infants and toddlers.

00:31:56.247 --> 00:31:57.515
It's that crazy,

00:31:57.515 --> 00:31:59.050
but it's a different world
that we live in.

00:31:59.050 --> 00:32:00.415
They have to get to work.

00:32:01.753 --> 00:32:03.721
Woman:
Now you guys are going to think

00:32:03.721 --> 00:32:06.224
about what
you're thankful for.

00:32:06.224 --> 00:32:08.393
Cyanne, do you want
to share?

00:32:08.393 --> 00:32:10.061
You don't have to
if you don't want to.

00:32:10.061 --> 00:32:11.222
That's okay.

00:32:11.596 --> 00:32:13.264
Narrator:
Ellis provides nurturing,

00:32:13.264 --> 00:32:14.933
child-centered care

00:32:14.933 --> 00:32:17.527
by skilled teachers,
like Aiyauna Terry.

00:32:19.237 --> 00:32:20.571
Would you like to share?

00:32:20.571 --> 00:32:23.308
Go ahead, Lilly,
what are you thankful for?

00:32:23.308 --> 00:32:26.110
My mommy and my daddy...

00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:28.479
Terry:
That future inventor,

00:32:28.479 --> 00:32:32.450
doctor, nurse,
whatever this child could be,

00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.720
now is the time that
their brains are at work.

00:32:35.720 --> 00:32:37.121
And can you tell him

00:32:37.121 --> 00:32:39.257
where the road is
to take you?

00:32:39.257 --> 00:32:42.794
It's gonna take you to Boston
all the way down here.

00:32:42.794 --> 00:32:43.661
Narrator:
Teachers are

00:32:43.661 --> 00:32:45.463
rigorously evaluated.

00:32:45.463 --> 00:32:47.598
Ellis is safe, clean,

00:32:47.598 --> 00:32:52.337
and offers a stimulating
environment for the early years.

00:32:52.337 --> 00:32:55.907
It's not only licensed,
it's nationally accredited.

00:32:55.907 --> 00:32:57.909
(pretends to scream)

